abstract: Libya's forces based in the country's east say they have seized a ship with Turkish crew members amid tensions in the eastern Mediterranean over a contentious maritime border deal involving Tripoli and Ankara.
snippet: Libya's forces based in the country's east say they have seized a ship with Turkish crew members amid tensions in the eastern Mediterranean over a contentious maritime border deal involving Tripoli and Ankara.
lead_paragraph: BENGHAZI, Libya — Libya's forces based in the country's east say they have seized a ship with Turkish crew members amid tensions in the eastern Mediterranean over a contentious maritime border deal involving Tripoli and Ankara.
headline_main: Libya's East-Based Forces Seize Ship With Turkish Crew
headline_print_headline: Libya's East-Based Forces Seize Ship With Turkish Crew

abstract: British supermarket giant Tesco suspended a Chinese supplier of Christmas cards on Sunday after a press report said a customer found a message written inside a card saying it had been packed by foreign prisoners who were victims of forced labor.
snippet: British supermarket giant Tesco suspended a Chinese supplier of Christmas cards on Sunday after a press report said a customer found a message written inside a card saying it had been packed by foreign prisoners who were victims of forced labor.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — British supermarket giant Tesco suspended a Chinese supplier of Christmas cards on Sunday after a press report said a customer found a message written inside a card saying it had been packed by foreign prisoners who were victims of forced labor.
headline_main: Tesco Suspends Chinese Supplier After Suspected Prisoner Message
headline_print_headline: Tesco Suspends Chinese Supplier After Suspected Prisoner Message

abstract: Developments in and out of this world that we’re still thinking about at year’s end.

abstract: Campaigns promoting female empowerment are all the rage. But women in advertising say they still have to navigate “Mad Men” workplaces.
snippet: Campaigns promoting female empowerment are all the rage. But women in advertising say they still have to navigate “Mad Men” workplaces.
lead_paragraph: The empowerment of women was a major theme of Advertising Week, a yearly gathering of roughly 100,000 ad-industry people in New York. The female R&B group TLC kicked off the program with a concert called “Future Is Female,” and there were panel discussions with titles like “Mom Bosses,” “#RewriteHerStory” and “Time’s Up, Pay Up: We Will Not Wait 100 Years.”

abstract: Recent residential sales in New York City and the region.

abstract: Zoltan Matyash witnessed “the worst of human agony” at Auschwitz and Buchenwald. Now he and his wife, Mera, are trying to get by on a fixed income in Borough Park, Brooklyn.
snippet: Zoltan Matyash witnessed “the worst of human agony” at Auschwitz and Buchenwald. Now he and his wife, Mera, are trying to get by on a fixed income in Borough Park, Brooklyn.
lead_paragraph: Zoltan Matyash grew up in Czechoslovakia, the oldest of two boys and four girls. He was born a Kohan, part of a line of priests who in the Jewish tradition are responsible for transmitting God’s blessing to all people.
